From: SJ Park <sj@kernel.org>
Date: Sat, 23 May 2026 13:51:07 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] ==== mark core-only using fields as private ====

mm/damon/core: hide struct fields from callers

DAMON core structs such as damon_region provides their iteration macro
like damon_for_each_region() to hide their type.  But the list heads are
exposed to users.

Some DAMON core struct fields are not for callers but marked as public
on kernel-doc comments.  That only encourage callers to wrongly access
the fields.

Mark those as private for kernel-doc.

Some of core struuct fields are only for core internal

Signed-off-by: SJ Park <sj@kernel.org>
---
 hkml_cv_bogus/hkml_cv_bogus_bx8kdnj9 | 0
 1 file changed, 0 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)
 create mode 100644 hkml_cv_bogus/hkml_cv_bogus_bx8kdnj9

diff --git a/hkml_cv_bogus/hkml_cv_bogus_bx8kdnj9 b/hkml_cv_bogus/hkml_cv_bogus_bx8kdnj9
new file mode 100644
index 0000000000000..e69de29bb2d1d
